<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 27 at 2:58PM MDT  by NWS Pueblo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of western Kiowa,
northeastern Crowley and northwestern Bent Counties through 330 PM
MDT...
At 257 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Arlington, or 26 miles northeast of North La Junta, moving northeast
at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Haswell around 315 PM MDT.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
